---
title: "Quantile estimator"
pagetitle: ivxtile-examples
---






Read in simulated data with different outcome-exposure relationships; `y#` outcome, `x` exposure, `g` instrumental variable (genotype).

::: {.cell collectcode='true'}

```{.stata .cell-code}
use ../data/ivmwdata, clear
```
:::


Plot outcome-exposure relationships

::: {.cell}

```{.stata .cell-code}
twoway line y1 x, sort(x)
```
:::

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](./img/ivmw-plot-01.svg){fig-align='center' fig-alt='Plot of relationship between y1 and x.'}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.stata .cell-code}
twoway line y2 y3 y4 x, sort(x)
```
:::

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](./img/ivmw-plot-02.svg){fig-align='center' fig-alt='Plot of relationships between y2, y3, y4, and x.'}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.stata .cell-code}
twoway line y5 x, sort(x)
```
:::

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](./img/ivmw-plot-03.svg){fig-align='center' fig-alt='Plot of relationship between y5 and x.'}
:::
:::


Use with different iv commands.

::: {.cell}

```{.stata .cell-code}
ivxtile, nq(5) par(x): ivregress 2sls y2 (x = g)
qui gr export ./img/ivxtile-plot-01.svg, replace
```


